The "Build Your First Dataset" project involved creating a synthetic (or observed) dataset to explore correlation.

Domain Selection: Chose the relationship between Study Hours and Exam Marks.

Data Generation: Created a 10-row sample to simulate a small classroom.

Role Identification: Categorized the columns into "Features" (Inputs) and "Labels" (Targets).

Hypothesis Testing: Formulated a prediction about how the Input affects the Output.

